# HTTP Methods 🌐

## 📖 What are HTTP Methods?

**HTTP Methods (HTTP Verbs)** define the type of action a client wants to perform on a server.

They are used in REST APIs to perform CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations.

In simple words:

> **HTTP Methods tell the server what action to perform.**

---

# 🎯 Why HTTP Methods?

Without HTTP Methods:

❌ No standard communication

❌ Difficult API design

❌ Confusing operations

With HTTP Methods:

✅ Standardized Communication

✅ Easy API Development

✅ Better REST Design

✅ Platform Independent

