# ⭐ Best Practices

* Use GET for reading data
* Use POST for creating resources
* Use PUT for full updates
* Use PATCH for partial updates
* Use DELETE for deleting resources
* Return proper HTTP status codes
* Use nouns in URLs

Good:

```text id="hm28"
/students
```

Bad:

```text id="hm29"
/getStudents
```

---

# ❌ Common Mistakes

* Using POST for updates
* Using GET for deletion
* Returning incorrect status codes
* Ignoring REST conventions

